Google's new AI Mode feature release promises to "include a preview of perspectives" from communities, social media, and other firsthand sources.This means unique stories and expertise are more important than ever before.Your content *needs* to answer the granular questions, problems, and JTBD unique to your audience. And it needs to be offered in a way that ties to credible and earned experience.With the recent "commodity vs non-commodity content," many have argued that Google is putting the onus of sourcing clicks on brands and publishers.To an extent, they're right. The "ten blue links" still surface textbook commodity content.But the right frame for organic growth programs isn't either/or.As long as traditional search still matters and AI search adoption continues to grow, B2B GEO & SEO programs need to adopt both content philosophies.
